        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:01PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Swansonville, or near Callands, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Chatham...
Blairs...
Callands...
Swansonville...
Dry Fork...
Climax...
and Sandy River.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
